"use strict";
module.exports = /*#__PURE__*/JSON.parse('{"business":{"name":"Taisu Wellness Studio","nameZh":"太素养生工作室","tagline":"Classical Chinese Medicine in Richmond, BC","taglineZh":"列治文古典中医","phone":"778-237-4832","email":"taisuwellness@gmail.com","address":"207- 11240 Bridgeport Road, Richmond, British Columbia, Canada","hours":"Tuesday - Sunday: 9am - 6pm","logo":"/uploads/1776809302711-g2gldhm5b.jpeg"},"home":{"heroTitle":"Real Classical Traditional Chinese Medicine in Richmond, BC","heroTitleZh":"古典中医针灸与草药疗法","heroSubtitle":"Acupuncture & Herbal Therapy for Whole-Body Healing","heroSubtitleZh":"列治文英属哥伦比亚","heroImage":"/uploads/1775494722242-x10660vv1.jpg","positioningTitle":"What is Classical traditional Chinese Medicine?","positioningZh":"什么是古典中医？","positioningContent":"中国古中医，特别是以《黄帝内经》和《伤寒杂病论》为核心的经方传统，其意义远超单纯的治疗方法。它代表了一套根植于中华文明、深刻理解生命与自然关系的独特健康哲学体系和实践体系。这门古老的学问，其价值在文化、医学、哲学、天文学等多个层面依然熠熠生辉，并对现代生活有着深刻的启示。\\n\\nThe significance of ancient Chinese medicine, particularly the Jingfang (Classical Formula) tradition centered on the Huangdi Neijing (Yellow Emperor\'s Inner Canon) and the Shanghan Zabing Lun (Treatise on Cold Damage and Miscellaneous Diseases), extends far beyond mere treatment methods. It represents a unique philosophical system and practical framework of health that is deeply rooted in Chinese civilization and offers a profound understanding of the relationship between life and nature. The value of this ancient discipline continues to shine brightly across multiple dimensions — culture, medicine, philosophy, astronomy, and beyond — and it holds deep insights for modern life.","positioningImage":"/uploads/1775494726914-xmms9e8f0.jpg","conditions":[{"en":"Insomnia","zh":"失眠","url":"/conditions/insomnia-treatment-richmond"},{"en":"Digestive Issues","zh":"消化问题","url":"/conditions/digestive-issues-richmond"},{"en":"Anxiety","zh":"焦虑症","url":"/conditions/anxiety-acupuncture-richmond"},{"en":"Women\'s Health","zh":"妇科调理","url":"/conditions/fertility-tcm-richmond"},{"en":"Chronic Fatigue","zh":"慢性疲劳","url":"/conditions/pain-management-acupuncture"}],"services":[{"en":"Acupuncture","zh":"针灸","image":"/images/acupuncture.jpg","desc":"Traditional needle therapy to restore energy flow and promote natural healing."},{"en":"Herbal Medicine","zh":"中草药","image":"/images/herbal.jpg","desc":"Classical Jing Fang formulas customized for your unique constitution."},{"en":"Consultation","zh":"咨询","image":"/images/consultation.jpg","desc":"Comprehensive evaluation using traditional Chinese medicine diagnosis methods."}],"trustItems":[{"title":"Personalized Treatments","desc":"Every treatment plan is uniquely crafted for your body and health goals."},{"title":"Classical Approach","desc":"We follow authentic Jing Fang principles, not modern TCM variations."},{"title":"Calm Environment","desc":"A serene space designed for relaxation and healing."}]},"about":{"title":"About Taisu Wellness","titleZh":"关于太素养生","philosophyTitle":"Our Healing Philosophy","philosophyZh":"我们的治疗理念","philosophyContent":"太素健康的理念是：唯有您自己的身体才能真正治愈您自己，我们只是协助您的身体，更快地完成它本就想要完成的工作。\\nThe philosophy of Taisu Wellness is: only your own body can truly heal you; we are merely assisting your body to complete, more quickly, the work it already wants to do.","image":"/uploads/1775534601056-2e5rqkdq7.jpg","features":[{"title":"Root-Cause Focus","desc":"世人注重症状，我们注重症状下的根源，只有解决病的根源，才能真正解决症状。\\nWe identify and treat the underlying cause of your health issues, not just mask the symptoms.","titleZh":"更注重病的根源"},{"title":"Classical Formulas","desc":"我们以中国第一部方书，伤寒杂病论为基础，以黄帝内经为理论基础，以道家的理论作为哲学理论基础，为患者开出每个人都不一样的个性化方剂。\\nWe base our practice on the Treatise on Cold Damage and Miscellaneous Diseases, the first classical medical formula text in China, with the Huangdi Neijing as our theoretical foundation, and Daoist philosophy as our guiding framework. Based on these principles, we create personalized herbal formulas tailored to each individual patient.","titleZh":"古方，经方"},{"title":"Whole-Person Care","desc":"我们会根据您的个人情况来制定我们的治疗计划，比如什么时候用针，什么时候用灸，什么时候用拔罐，什么时候用药等，或者我们会针灸与药配合，或者拔罐与艾灸配合等组合疗法。\\nWe tailor each treatment plan to your individual condition, determining when to use acupuncture, moxibustion, cupping, or herbal medicine. We may also combine therapies—such as acupuncture with herbs, or cupping with moxibustion—for a more integrated approach.","titleZh":"个性护理"}],"whyUsTitle":"Why We Exist","whyUsZh":"我们为什么存在","whyUsContent":["我们存在的意义，不是成为一个“解决问题”的地方。","而是在这个过度干预、过度依赖外力的时代，提供另一种可能——","让身体自己回到它本来的状态。","在太素，我们始终相信：没有任何治疗能真正替代身体自身的恢复能力。","药物、针灸、艾灸，都只是辅助。","真正起作用的，是人体自身的阳气、气机与整体平衡。","因此，我们不追求快速压制症状，而是在意——","你的身体，是否重新开始运作。","这也是为什么，我们的方式不一定适合所有人。","但如果你在寻找一种更本质的恢复方式。","Our purpose is not to be a place that simply \\"solves problems.\\"","Rather, in this era of excessive intervention and over‑reliance on external forces, we offer another possibility —","Let the body return to its own natural state.","At Taisu, we have always believed: no treatment can truly replace the body\'s own ability to heal.","Medications, acupuncture, moxibustion — they are only aids.","What truly works is the body\'s own yang qi, its qi flow, and overall balance.","That is why we do not pursue the rapid suppression of symptoms. Instead, we care about —","Whether your body has started functioning on its own again.","This is also why our approach may not be for everyone.","But if you are seeking a more fundamental way to recover."],"featuresTitle":"What is Classical Chinese Traditional Medicine?","featuresTitleZh":"什么是古中医？"},"services":[{"en":"Acupuncture and Moxibustion","zh":"针&灸","fullDesc":"针-以通为补，通过调动身体气血来帮助身体修复。\\n灸-艾草纯阳之草，点燃后，阳性能量向下注入身体中，通过补阳，提高身体修复功能来帮助身体修复。\\nAcupuncture — uses unblocking as tonification, helping the body repair itself by mobilizing its qi and blood.\\nMoxibustion — mugwort is the herb of pure yang. When lit, its yang energy flows downward into the body, enhancing the body\'s repair functions by supplementing yang, thereby assisting in healing.","image":"/uploads/1784336769925-aps6yp64i.png","benefits":["Pain relief","Stress reduction","Improved sleep","Enhanced immunity"],"conditions":["Chronic pain","Headaches","Anxiety","Insomnia","Digestive issues"]},{"en":"Herbal Medicine","zh":"中草药","fullDesc":"中医会利用中药阴阳的偏性来帮助调节身体阴阳的偏性，从而达到身体的阴阳平衡的结果\\nIn TCM, herbal medicine uses the inherent Yin–Yang properties of herbs to correct imbalances in the body, thereby restoring overall Yin–Yang balance.","image":"/uploads/1776810482371-ie2ihbhs8.jpeg","benefits":["Root-cause treatment","Personalized formulas","Natural ingredients","Long-term healing"],"conditions":["Internal conditions","Women\'s health","Fatigue","Immune support","Digestive disorders"]},{"en":"Consultation","zh":"咨询","fullDesc":"望闻问切，教育，改变错误生活习惯。\\n\\nComprehensive health assessment using traditional TCM diagnosis methods including pulse reading, tongue examination, and detailed consultation about your health history and lifestyle.","image":"/uploads/1784336791679-w5pzdk5om.png","benefits":["Health assessment","Treatment planning","Lifestyle guidance","Preventive care"],"conditions":["First-time patients","Complex health issues","Preventive wellness"]}],"conditions":[{"slug":"insomnia-treatment-richmond","en":"Insomnia & Sleep Disorders","zh":"失眠与睡眠障碍","preview":"入睡困难、夜晚辗转难眠、醒来依然疲惫。Difficulty sleeping, restless nights, waking up tired.","symptoms":"睡眠对于修复和再生至关重要。当睡眠被打乱时，身体的各个系统都会受到影响。\\nSleep is essential for healing and regeneration. When sleep is disrupted, every system in the body suffers.","symptomsList":["Difficulty falling asleep","Waking up frequently during the night","Light, non-restorative sleep","Anxiety and racing thoughts at bedtime","Fatigue upon waking"],"tcmPerspective":"在中医看来，失眠多由脏腑失调所致，其中以心肾不交最为常见。胃不和、肝血不足（多因压力与劳累）以及肺寒等因素，也会影响神志安定与睡眠质量。整体调理、辨证施治是改善失眠的关键\\nIn TCM, insomnia is often caused by internal organ imbalances, with Heart–Kidney disharmony being the most common. Digestive issues, Liver Blood deficiency (often due to stress and overwork), and Lung cold can also disrupt the mind and affect sleep quality. Holistic, pattern-based treatment is key to improving sleep.","treatment":"针灸可以安神定志、调节机体平衡，帮助改善睡眠质量。中药从根本入手，调理失衡、滋养身体。两者结合，能够更全面、持久地改善失眠问题。\\nAcupuncture helps calm the nervous system and regulate the body’s internal balance, promoting deeper, more restful sleep. Herbal medicine works at the root level by correcting underlying imbalances and nourishing the body. Together, they provide a holistic and lasting approach to improving insomnia.","image":"/uploads/1784336816232-37mwxbe8h.png"},{"slug":"digestive-issues-richmond","en":"Digestive Issues","zh":"消化系统问题","preview":"腹胀、肠易激综合征、胃酸反流、食欲不振。Bloating, IBS, acid reflux, poor appetite.","symptoms":"在中医看来，消化系统是整体健康的基础。现代饮食习惯与压力常常会损伤脾胃功能。\\nDigestive health is the foundation of overall wellness in TCM. Modern diets and stress often damage the digestive system.","symptomsList":["Bloating and distension","Irregular bowel movements","Acid reflux","Food sensitivities","Fatigue after eating"],"tcmPerspective":"中医认为，过多寒凉饮食会损伤脾胃功能，而压力则易导致气机不畅。两者共同作用，容易引发消化问题。\\nIn TCM, excessive consumption of cold foods can weaken digestive function, while stress can lead to Qi stagnation. Together, these factors often contribute to digestive issues.","treatment":"针灸通过调理脾胃气机、促进运化功能，改善腹胀、食欲不振等症状；中药则从根本入手，祛寒健脾化湿、理气和胃。两者结合，能够整体提升消化功能并恢复内在平衡。\\nAcupuncture regulates the Qi of the Spleen and Stomach, enhancing digestive function and relieving symptoms such as bloating and poor appetite. Herbal medicine addresses the root by dispelling cold, strengthening the Spleen, resolving dampness, and harmonizing the Stomach. Together, they improve digestion and restore overall internal balance.","image":"/uploads/1784336836865-9a3vygkhs.png"},{"slug":"anxiety-acupuncture-richmond","en":"Anxiety & Stress","zh":"焦虑与压力","preview":"持续的担忧、神经紧绷、难以放松。Constant worry, nervous energy, difficulty relaxing.","symptoms":"焦虑和压力影响着数以百万计的人群，同时损害身心健康。中医提供自然的方法来帮助恢复内在的平静。\\nAnxiety and stress affect millions, impacting both mental and physical health. TCM offers natural approaches to restore calm.","symptomsList":["Excessive worry","Racing thoughts","Physical tension","Sleep disturbances","Digestive issues from stress"],"tcmPerspective":"焦虑抑郁这些，主要问题来源于我们身体的阴寒，而当阴寒之气阻滞了身体生发之气，也就是中医说的肝气，才会造成肝气不舒、肝气郁滞这些。人的心情会被这种无法生发之气所影响导致焦虑与抑郁。\\nIn TCM, conditions like anxiety and depression are often rooted in internal cold and yin accumulation. When this cold obstructs the body’s natural rising and flowing energy—known as Liver Qi—it leads to stagnation and constraint. This lack of free movement of Qi can affect emotional balance, resulting in anxiety and depression.","treatment":"可以通过针灸疏通经络，将生发之气打通。另外可以通过中药来祛寒，治本的方式，恢复阳气，阳气回来了自然开心快乐。\\nAcupuncture can help open the meridians and restore the smooth flow of rising Qi. Herbal medicine can dispel cold and address the root by restoring Yang energy—when Yang returns, a natural sense of ease and well-being follows.","image":"/uploads/1784336858279-rwfje5jnt.png"},{"slug":"fertility-tcm-richmond","en":"Women\'s Health & Fertility","zh":"妇科与生殖健康","preview":"Menstrual disorders, fertility support, pregnancy wellness, and menopause.","symptoms":"Women\'s bodies go through significant changes throughout life. TCM offers natural support for hormonal balance and reproductive health.","symptomsList":["Menstrual irregularities and pain","PCOS, endometriosis, fibroids","Fertility challenges (TTC)","PMS and hormonal mood swings","Perimenopause and menopause symptoms"],"tcmPerspective":"In TCM, women\'s health is closely tied to the Liver, Spleen, and Kidney systems. TCM works to balance these systems and regulate hormonal function.","treatment":"Acupuncture and herbal medicine to improve ovarian function, blood flow to the uterus, and hormonal balance.","image":"/uploads/1784336876232-8yiuv606w.png"},{"slug":"pain-management-acupuncture","en":"Pain Management & Chronic Fatigue","zh":"疼痛管理与慢性疲劳","preview":"Chronic pain, headaches, back pain, arthritis, and chronic fatigue.","symptoms":"Chronic pain and fatigue often go hand in hand, creating a cycle that\'s difficult to break with conventional medicine alone.","symptomsList":["Chronic headaches and migraines","Back pain, neck pain, shoulder tension","Arthritis and joint pain","Fibromyalgia","Chronic Fatigue Syndrome"],"tcmPerspective":"Pain in TCM is understood as stagnation - when Qi and blood can\'t flow freely, pain results. Fatigue focuses on restoring depleted energy.","treatment":"Acupuncture to promote blood circulation and reduce inflammation. Formulas to tonify deficiency.","image":"/uploads/1784336890670-nxwb6v5dv.png"},{"slug":"condition-1776825701684","en":"rhinitis, allergies, sinusitis, eczema","zh":"鼻炎，过敏，鼻窦炎，湿疹","preview":"鼻炎，过敏，鼻窦炎，湿疹，他们其实都是感冒没好的结果。Rhinitis, allergies, sinusitis, and eczema are often the result of an unresolved common cold.","symptoms":"眼睛痒、鼻子痒、流鼻涕、身上痒、同时会伴有怕热，时而怕冷。\\nItchy eyes, itchy nose, runny nose, itchy skin, often accompanied by feeling hot easily and occasional chills.","symptomsList":[],"tcmPerspective":"都是因为感冒没有完全好，身体的能量不足以把寒气逼出体外。\\nThese conditions often occur because the body has not fully recovered from a cold, and its energy is not strong enough to expel the remaining cold from the body.","treatment":"扶阳，提高身体能量，将身体的汗湿发出来，本质上是在帮助身体排异，以达到完全康复的目的。\\nRestoring Yang and strengthening the body’s energy helps the body release cold and dampness through sweating. In essence, this supports the body’s natural elimination process and promotes complete recovery.","image":"/uploads/1784336905173-tkl9u42na.png"}],"blog":[{"slug":"why-cant-sleep-tcm","en":"What is Yin and Yang?","zh":"什么是阴阳","date":"Apr 15, 2026","excerpt":"阳就是功能，阴就是物质！Yang represents function, while Yin represents substance.","content":"阳就是功能，阴就是物质！功能依托于物质而施展，即是血为气之母，物质依托于功能而生命，所以气为血之帅。\\nYang represents function, while Yin represents substance. Function depends on substance to operate—this is why blood is considered the mother of Qi. Substance relies on function to sustain life—therefore, Qi is regarded as the commander of blood.","image":"/uploads/1784337032247-394vrg5j3.png"},{"slug":"what-is-jing-fang","en":"What is Jing Fang Medicine?","zh":"什么是经方医学？","date":"Feb 8, 2026","excerpt":"Exploring the classical approach to herbal medicine that has been refined over 2000 years...","content":"Full blog post content here...","image":"/uploads/1776896989383-vn6fai1z0.png"},{"slug":"5-signs-spleen-deficiency","en":"Healing Crisis (also known as an Elimination Reaction)","zh":"瞑眩反应（又叫排异反应）","date":"December 28, 2025","excerpt":"因气血重新调整与身体自我修复而出现的一种暂时性不适反应。as the body readjusts Qi and Blood and begins its natural healing process.","content":"瞑眩反应（也称排异反应），是指患者在接受中药、针灸或艾灸治疗后，因气血重新调整与身体自我修复而出现的一种暂时性不适反应。尤其在中药调理过程中，身体可能会通过发烧、咳嗽、呕吐、腹泻等方式进行排浊与调整。虽然这些反应本身会让人感到不舒服，但往往是身体恢复平衡过程中的正常表现。\\nA Healing Crisis (also known as an Elimination Reaction) refers to a temporary discomfort that may occur after treatment with herbal medicine, acupuncture, or moxibustion, as the body readjusts Qi and Blood and begins its natural healing process. Especially during herbal treatment, the body may respond through fever, coughing, vomiting, diarrhea, or other reactions as it works to eliminate toxins and restore balance. Although these symptoms may feel uncomfortable, they are often considered a normal part of the body’s recovery process.","image":"/uploads/1784336998629-gi5bx7rgm.png"}]}');

